<item>
            <title>[TIKA-1652] Tika Server should allow config file override from the command line like Tika App</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-1652</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Tika-app&apos;s TikaCLI allows a command line parameter, --config, to override the Tika config at the command line. For whatever reason, Tika-server doesn&apos;t it should since it causes a different control flow for things to get created. I first saw this when testing the CTAKESParser (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-1645&quot; title=&quot;Extraction of biomedical information using CTAKESParser&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;TIKA-1645&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;TIKA-1645&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) in Tika-server.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
